New Records: Alperen Sengun scored 25 points and grabbed 14 rebounds for the Houston Rockets.
Jalen Brunson led the New York Knicks with 29 points.
OG Anunoby contributed 21 points for the Knicks.
Karl-Anthony Towns had 17 points and a season-high 19 rebounds.
The Houston Rockets won the game 109-97.
Key Match Events: Amen Thompson made a soaring two-handed dunk followed by Jalen Green's game-sealing three-pointer to secure the win.
The Rockets led by 15 points early but struggled to maintain their lead before pulling away late.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Rockets were outscored 62-38 in the paint by the Knicks.
Houston made only 8 of 33 three-pointers, struggling offensively from the perimeter.
